      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Usually we only consider the effect of the bit on the horse, but what about the way it affects the rider?  An important aspect of the bit is the way it affects the psychology of the rider. In my experience curb bits encourage quieter hands. I always remember the first time my coach had me ride her horse with only the curb part of a double bridle. It was amazing the effect this had on me. I was so conscious of my hands and keeping them soft and quiet and forwards thinking.",
      "id": "1237554099800"
